description:
&lt;p&gt;Swansea Bay University Health Board is looking to recruit an enthusiastic and driven individual to the post of Senior Data Analyst. The primary responsibility of the post holder will be to support delivery of information analysis and Business Intelligence solutions that will support service improvement and management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will require an excellent understanding of analytical and statistical techniques that can be applied to healthcare information. To understand specific information requirements the post holder will be required to liaise with service users.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role will be suited to a talented individual that is dedicated to working as part of an effective digital intelligence team as well as being able to manage individual prjects.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are interested and would like to know more please contact Joanne Emms, Data Intelligence Manager (joanne.emms@wales.nhs.uk).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; Welsh and/or English speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne EmmsData Intelligence Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanne.emms@wales.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
